<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1535797" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nengi-1-1.jpg?resize=577%2C409&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="577" height="409" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nengi-1-1.jpg?w=577&amp;ssl=1 577w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nengi-1-1.jpg?resize=300%2C213&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nengi-1-1.jpg?resize=58%2C41&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nengi-1-1.jpg?resize=260%2C184&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nengi-1-1.jpg?resize=183%2C130&amp;ssl=1 183w" sizes="(max-width: 577px) 100vw, 577px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Guinness Nigeria has unveiled ex-Big Brother Naija housemate Nengi Hampson as a brand ambassador. She becomes a member of an enviable class of new brand managers which includes Prince Enwerem, Beverly Naya, Fireboy DML, Oli Ekun, and Yagazie Emezi. The 23-year-old model and reality TV star exude the bold, distinct and premium character which the brand represents. Speaking about the new development, Adenike Adebola, Marketing & Innovation Director, Guinness Nigeria, explained: “We are beyond excited to unveil Nengi as a brand ambassador. For us, she is an emblem of our rich history – bold, captivating and uninhibited. This association is a toast to unapologetic women owning their crafts every day. A Guinness woman is self-assured and audacious, leaving a mark wherever she shows up. Nengi is a Guinness woman!” On her part, Nengi said, “For me, Guinness represents confidence and beauty and I’m excited to drive what it means to be a Guinness woman with a new generation of empowered women. Every bold and extraordinary woman is a queen and every queen deserves a premium brew.” Vanguard News Nigeria As part of his visit to Nigeria with Guinness, Rio Ferdinand attended a ses